srefix-diagnosis
Copyright 2026 The srefix-diagnosis Authors

This product includes diagnostic content synthesized by Large Language Models
(Claude family by Anthropic and/or GPT family by OpenAI). The synthesis was
validated against publicly-available, open-source documentation. No proprietary,
internal, or non-public material was used as input.

PUBLIC DOCUMENTATION SOURCES INFORMING THE DIAGNOSTIC CONTENT
=============================================================

The 250 markdown manuals under `agents/*.md` describe symptom → diagnosis
patterns, metrics, and root-cause decision trees for the technologies listed
below. The content was generated by reasoning about publicly-documented
behaviors. No documentation text was directly copied; the synthesis paraphrases
operational knowledge available in each project's official, openly-licensed
documentation.

If you believe any specific section reproduces copyrighted text verbatim, see
ISSUES.md for the takedown process.

